						<summary>

						<p>Damaged. This inscription registers the order of the king Kulaśēkharadēva that the tax dues must be set apart for conducting the service called Senbagapperumāḷ sandi. Mentions the taxes like <hi rend="italic">Andarāyam, Poṉvari Veṭṭibāṭṭam, Tariyiṟai, Chekkiṟai, Taṭṭārbāṭṭam, Iṉavari</hi> etc., in this inscription. </p>						

						</summary>
